 
			 ===================

			   Octopus _RELEASE_

			 ===================

This is "Octopus", a java library with parallel constructs which harnesses the paralellization of multicores.

Why use Octopus?
--------------

Because Octopus allows you to use its parallel constructs to write highly concurrent applications to fully 
harness the parallelization of multicore systems.

Which all platforms is Octopus supported on?
--------------------------------------------

Since it is a pure java library this is supported on all platforms on which java is supported
<TBD>Add section for native code for CPU affinity</TBD>

Who can use Octopus?
------------------

Octopus is distributed under the GPL (GNU Public License).  Please
read the license to make sure it's okay to use it in your circumstances.

Where do I find new copies of Kaffe?
------------------------------------

Kaffe is available from impetus sites.  The primary site is:

        http://www.impetus.com/octopus/


How do I report bugs and problems?
----------------------------------

Go the website http://www.kaffe.org/ and you'll find information on how to
report bugs.

What software do I need to install Kaffe?
-----------------------------------------

You will need ant 1.5.4 and higher to compile octopus and ant should be in your PATH. An already compiled jar is available if you 
simply want to start using it.

How do I compile and install kaffe?
-----------------------------------

For UNIX it couldn't be simpler:

  $ cd build 
  $ ant clean
  $ ant compile
  $ ant jar

Running Kaffe
=============

* Just include the octopus.jar in your classpath of your application
